Compliance evaluation reveals that the Atlassian Customer Agreement necessitates a thorough examination of subcontracting chains to ensure compliance with contractual obligations.

Clause 20.11 (Subcontractors and Affiliates) states that Atlassian may use subcontractors or its Affiliates in the performance of its obligations under this Agreement. However, this clause does not specify any requirements for evaluating the length and complexity of subcontracting chains.

To address this gap, I suggest adding a requirement to evaluate the length and complexity of subcontracting chains, including references to the number of subcontractors or geographical dispersion. This can be achieved by modifying clause 20.11 as follows:

"20.11. Subcontractors and Affiliates. Atlassian may use subcontractors or its Affiliates in the performance of its obligations under this Agreement. In doing so, Atlassian shall:

(a) maintain a record of all subcontractors and Affiliates used in the performance of its obligations;
(b) ensure that subcontractors and Affiliates are selected and managed in accordance with Atlassian's subcontracting policies and procedures;
(c) evaluate the length and complexity of subcontracting chains, including the number of subcontractors and geographical dispersion, to ensure that they do not pose a risk to the performance of this Agreement;
(d) obtain written confirmation from subcontractors and Affiliates that they will comply with the terms of this Agreement and any applicable laws and regulations."

This modified clause requires Atlassian to evaluate the length and complexity of subcontracting chains, including the number of subcontractors and geographical dispersion, to ensure compliance with contractual obligations.
